The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Thursday, December 22, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Santiniketan, Dec 21: This years Pous Mela, on the theme suchi shilpa or stitched handicrafts, will begin on December 23.

 Visva-Bharati has decided to give free space to craftsmen and traders from rural areas who earlier had to pay the authorities for setting up stalls at the fair.

 Calcutta: Several persons were injured when police resorted to lathi charge to disperse a mob near gate number 1 of Salt Lake Stadium after a constable was assaulted over a bicycle theft.

 Chinsurah: Fifteen-year-old Prasanta Chanak, missing since March, returned home on Tuesday. The resident of Hooghly, 100 km from Calcutta, was found unconscious in Kanpur. Doctors treating him contacted police.

 Krishnagar: A woman scalded her brother-in-laws wife after an argument over who was more beautiful. Soma allegedly threw hot water and boiling milk at Mithu Banerjee in Bethuadahari, about 130 km from Calcutta, police said.

 Durgapur: Animal resources development minister Anisur Rahaman on Tuesday inaugurated the second phase of an egg project by Alchemist in Burdwan as part of the companys Rs 611-crore investment in Bengal.




